    <item>
      <title>01 Introduction</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/bloody-lands/intro/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 11 Sep 2023 00:00:00 +0800</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/bloody-lands/intro/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;assumptions&#34;&gt;Assumptions&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Set in a speculative very near future where our mode of technology isn&amp;rsquo;t too different from today.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Yes, this is effectively a not-so-subtle nod to Twilight 2000 and The Country by Luke Gearing.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Yes, this is also based on a hypothetical future for my home country based on lived experiences. Yes, this was kind of depressing to write. No, I&amp;rsquo;m not always this cynical.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You can find the companion adventure &lt;a href=&#34;https://san-tagoy.itch.io/ten-hail-marys-in-the-dark&#34;&gt;Ten Hail Marys in the Dark on itch&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Character Creation</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/bloody-lands/chargen/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 11 Sep 2023 00:00:00 +0800</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/bloody-lands/chargen/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;assumptions&#34;&gt;Assumptions&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start at 17 years of age&lt;/strong&gt;. By the end of character creation, you&amp;rsquo;re assumed be a survivor in this world.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Each &lt;strong&gt;Skill&lt;/strong&gt; adds a +1, +2, or +3 to a 2d6 roll. You only roll 2d6 when doing risky things like shooting a foe in a firefight or trying to pick a lock under duress. The number you need to beat is always an 8, no more, no less.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Gear List</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/bloody-lands/gear-list/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 11 Sep 2023 00:00:00 +0800</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/bloody-lands/gear-list/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;gear&#34;&gt;Gear&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Currency? Backed by fucking what? There are semblances of it ever since the Landlords took control of factories. Bullets from them are like trickled down gold. Nonetheless, it&amp;rsquo;s still hearkening back to what we&amp;rsquo;ve completely lost. Keeping up appearances in these times is asinine.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Social credit&amp;rsquo;s back since all we really got is our word that we&amp;rsquo;ll repay at one point. If your word is shit, however, expect fists to your face in the foreseeable future.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
